# Gitleaks fingerprints to suppress. Each line is `<file>:<rule-id>:<line>`
# (or longer fingerprint form). Used by gitleaks-the-tool, not gitignore.
#
# Adding here means: "this is a known finding, reviewed, intentional".
# Personal-rule fingerprints (prefix `personal-`) come from the maintainer's
# global gitleaks config and only fire on machines that have it loaded.

# CONTRIBUTING.md L43 — example `~/.ssh/your_signing_key.pub` in the SSH
# commit-signing setup instructions. Standard convention.
CONTRIBUTING.md:personal-tilde-dotfile-path:43

# deny.toml L27 — cargo-deny's `db-path = "~/.cargo/advisory-db"`. The
# cargo-deny convention for locating the local RustSec advisory DB.
deny.toml:personal-tilde-dotfile-path:27
